Pour the @water for the bulgur{240%ml} into a large #saucepan{}, stir in half the
@chicken stock paste{20%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for
~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, green beans
and pepper. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the veg has softened and the chicken is golden brown on the outside
and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @roasted spice and herb blend{1} to the
pan. Cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the remaining chicken stock paste and the @sugar{½%tsp} and
@water for the sauce{100%ml} until combined.

Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down to medium and simmer until thickened
slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{½}.

When the bulgur is cooked, stir through. Stir the lemon zest and a squeeze of
juice. Reheat if needed.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice to the saucy chicken. Taste and season with more
lemon juice, salt and pepper if needed, adding a splash of water if it's a little
too thick.

Share the zesty bulgur between your bowls.

Top with the saucy chicken and tuck in. Enjoy!